{
  "name": "Silt Frog",
  "type": "ancestry",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Your companion is a silt frog, an oversized frog with a natural ability to detect magic, its main food source.</p><p><strong>Size</strong> Small</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> jaws, Damage 1d6 piercing</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> tongue (reach 10 feet), Damage 1d4 bludgeoning</p><p><strong>Str</strong> +3, <strong>Dex</strong> +2, <strong>Con</strong> +2, <strong>Int</strong> –4, <strong>Wis</strong> +1, <strong>Cha</strong> +0</p><p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 6</p><p><strong>Skill</strong> Stealth</p><p><strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision, magic sense (imprecise) 30 feet (the silt frog can sense the presence of magical auras within 30 feet as an imprecise sense)</p><p><strong>Speed</strong> 25 feet, burrow 15 feet, swim 25 feet</p><p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> Your silt frog unleashes an eardrum-rattling croak when you create an opening. Until the start of your next turn, if you hit and deal damage to a creature within your silt frog's reach, the creature is @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.9PR9y0bi4JPKnHPR]{Deafened} until the start of your next turn.</p><p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-animal-companions.sf-AC-Advanced-Maneuvers.Item.A2A7w59cxW12cBbw]{Ingest Magic}</p>"
    },
